German  Chancellor Angela Merkel  gave
in to French counterpart Nicolas Sarkozy in failing to secure
European court rights to rule on national debt-limit violations,
 Die Welt said , citing unidentified people close to the talks.  Merkel also failed during negotiations yesterday to
persuade Sarkozy to give the European Commission powers to
remand member countries on national budgets should they not
comply with the stability pact, the German newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
